<title type="html"><![CDATA[I proudly present you: [The PiBoy]]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10505&amp;p=118228#p118228"><![CDATA[
I already postet it over at modretro.com, but I thought this might fit into this forum too <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br />This is my first real Hardware Mod and actually &quot;portablization&quot; (so far it does not have Batteries, but I plan to use one of these external Phonechargerboxes which would just work fine <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />)<br />It is made of an old DMG Gameboy and a RaspberryPi running with RetroPie.<br />It took me not long to prepare the DMG case to hold the screen and the RPi, but it was a bit difficult. The best thing is, that I could reuse the joystick of the Gameboy motherboard, so all NES, GB and GBC games can be fully played, eventually Sega games too, because there are enough buttons <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> Otherwise, you could just connect a USB joystick to the PiBoy or connect one to it's internal Bluetooth ;D<br />I tried to fit everything without changing the Cases apperance, without cutting too many holes in it.<br />HDMI does also work and you could just use it as you would normally if <br />do not intend to use it to play Games <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br /><br />Some pictures of my masterpiece:<br /><a href="http://www.pic-upload.de/view-20745502/IMG_20130916_210311.jpg.html" class="postlink"><img src="http://www7.pic-upload.de/thumb/16.09.13/4k3crdrcz954.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><a href="http://www.pic-upload.de/view-20745536/IMG_20130916_210412.jpg.html" class="postlink"><img src="http://www7.pic-upload.de/thumb/16.09.13/3kjd8mfq76jg.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><a href="http://www.pic-upload.de/view-20745572/IMG_20130916_210452.jpg.html" class="postlink"><img src="http://www7.pic-upload.de/thumb/16.09.13/vj16g3ahe7y1.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><a href="http://www.pic-upload.de/view-20745595/IMG_20130916_210601.jpg.html" class="postlink"><img src="http://www7.pic-upload.de/thumb/16.09.13/awpiun5zfzeg.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><a href="http://www.pic-upload.de/view-20745630/IMG_20130916_210639.jpg.html" class="postlink"><img src="http://www7.pic-upload.de/thumb/16.09.13/ldszeyv52qgr.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><br />Edit: As requested, here are the pics of it's inner life <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> I forgot: All connectors were rewired, like Lan connector or USB connector, in order to use them <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br /><br /><a href="http://www.pic-upload.de/view-20757639/IMG_20130918_081645.jpg.html" class="postlink"><img src="http://www7.pic-upload.de/thumb/18.09.13/ohj2dxdufegu.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><a href="http://www.pic-upload.de/view-20757645/IMG_20130918_081701.jpg.html" class="postlink"><img src="http://www7.pic-upload.de/thumb/18.09.13/donghe22zf3j.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><br /><a href="http://www.pic-upload.de/view-20757649/IMG_20130918_081726.jpg.html" class="postlink"><img src="http://www7.pic-upload.de/thumb/18.09.13/65so73bs8uq.jpg" alt="Image" /></a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6173">yasin</a> — Wed Sep 18, 2013 4:02 am</p><hr />
